title: ElectricVehicles
text: Electric Vehicles Data comes from Washington State Department of Licensing and shows the number of Battery Electric and Plug-in Hybrid Vehicles currently registered in Washington state This analysis uses parameterized markdown to show the state that the vehicle is now located and which counties have the highest number of electric vehicles with licenses from Washington State. Associated Github Repository The table below shows each state and links to the html file with the associated map. electrics <- ds %>% group_by(State) %>% summarize(ElectricVehicles = n()) electric <- function(state){ electrics %>% filter(State == state) %>% select(ElectricVehicles) } States <- data.frame(state_code = unique(ds$State), state_full = state.name[match(unique(ds$State),state.abb)]) States <- States %>% mutate(ElectricVehicles = unlist(map(state_code, electric)), state_full = case_when( state_code == "DC" ~ "Washington DC", state_code == "BC" ~ "British Columbia", TRUE ~ state_full), link = paste0("./files/", state_code,".html"), report = paste0('', state_full,'' )) States %>% select(report, ElectricVehicles) %>% datatable(States, filter="top", escape=FALSE, colnames = c("Report", "# Electric Vehicles"), rownames = FALSE) Input to asJSON(keep_vec_names=TRUE) is a named vector. In a future version of jsonlite, this option will not be supported, and named vectors will be translated into arrays instead of objects. If you want JSON object output, please use a named list instead. See ?toJSON.

library(ggplot2)
library(urbnmapr)

#| include: false
ds <- read.csv("https://data.wa.gov/api/views/f6w7-q2d2/rows.csv?accessType=DOWNLOAD")

##remove alaska and hawaii and BC

ds <- ds %>%
  mutate(County = ifelse(State == "AK", paste0(County, " Borough"), paste0(County, " County")), state_name = state.name[match(State,state.abb)])
counties_sf<- get_urbn_map("counties", sf=TRUE)

state_full = state.name[match(params$state, state.abb)]



Functions to Create Graphic


Code
state_counties = function(state){
  counties_sf %>%
  filter(state_name == state)
}

state_electrics = function(state, ds) {
  ds %>%
  filter(state_name == state) %>%
  mutate(county_name = County) %>%
  group_by(county_name) %>%
  summarise(ElectricVehicles = n()) 
}

FullState = function(state) {
  left_join(state_counties(state), state_electrics(state, ds), by = "county_name")
}




State Map


Code
FullState(state_full) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(fill = ElectricVehicles), color = "brown4", position = "identity") +
  coord_sf()+
  theme_minimal() +
  #scale_fill_steps(n.breaks = 8)+
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Greens", n.breaks = 7, direction = 1)+
  theme(
    axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
    axis.title.x = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_blank(),
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    axis.line.x = element_blank(),
    axis.line.y = element_blank()
  )

title: loading
text:
Equity.Analyser <- function(x) {
  render("Parameters.qmd", 
         params = list(state = x),
         output_file = paste0("~/Documents/DS-Masters/CWD/ParameterizedMarkdown/ElectricVehicles/files/",x,".html"))
}

ds <- read.csv("https://data.wa.gov/api/views/f6w7-q2d2/rows.csv?accessType=DOWNLOAD") |>
  mutate(state_name = state.name[match(State,state.abb)])


States <- unique(ds$State)
States %>% walk(., function(x) {Equity.Analyser(x)})
